							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/martinpadgett/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/martin-padgett-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/martin-padgett-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Martin Padgett" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/martinpadgett/">Martin Padgett</a></h6>
										Martin Padgett is the author of <Em>A Night at the Sweet Gum Head</em> and <em>The Many Passions of Michael Hardwick: Sex and the Supreme Court in the Age of AIDS</em>. Recipient of a Lambda Literary Fellowship, his writing has appeared in the <em>Oxford American, The Paris Review,</em> and <em>TheWashington Post</em>, among other publications. He lives in Pensacola Beach, Florida.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
